  m_Name: Forepaw_Digit2_Phalanx_L
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::ModelPartDataSO
  id: Forepaw_Digit2_Phalanx_L
  partName: Forepaw Digit2 Phalanx Left
  descriptionChunks:
  - The left forepaw digit two phalanx forms part of the second toe within the canine
    forepaw and contributes significantly to movement and stability. This bone provides
    attachment points for tendons and ligaments controlling toe flexion and extension
    during locomotion.
  - The second digit assists with weight distribution, balance, and coordinated paw
    placement while the dog walks, runs, or changes direction. It also helps absorb
    impact forces and maintain traction on various surfaces.
